# Audit Reports Rule

## When This Rule Applies

This rule **automatically applies** when:
- User says "audit" in a prompt (e.g., "audit the codebase", "run an audit")
- An audit command is executed (e.g., `audit-project`, `audit-security`)
- The AI performs autonomous auditing as part of a workflow
- Creating any document that reports audit findings

---

## Core Principle

**All audit reports must be saved in a consistent location with standardized naming and structure.** This ensures:
- Easy discovery of past audits
- Consistent audit history
- Comparable results over time
- Clear audit trail for compliance

---

## Storage Location

### Required Location

**All audit reports MUST be saved to:**
```
docs/_reports/audits/
```

