## Agent Behavior

### When User Requests Audit

1. Determine audit type from context
2. Execute appropriate audit checks
3. Create report using template above
4. Save to `docs/_reports/audits/{type}_audit_{date}.md`
5. Update `docs/_reports/audits/README.md` index
6. Report completion to user with link to report

### When Running Audit Command

1. Follow command-specific instructions
2. Generate report using this rule's template
3. Save to correct location
4. Update index

### Autonomous Auditing

When performing audits as part of workflow (e.g., pre-flight check):
1. If generating a formal report, follow this rule
2. If just checking status, no report needed
3. If findings are significant, consider generating report

